---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Bracketly handles data: what runs client-side, what analytics and ads are used, and what data (if any) is collected."
>
  <div class="container" style="max-width:680px;">
    <div style="padding:3rem 0 1rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2rem;letter-spacing:-0.03em;margin:0 0 0.75rem;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:0.95rem;margin:0 0 2rem;">Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <div class="panel" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
        <h2 style="margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-size:1.1rem;">The tools themselves</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin:0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">
          Bracketly has no backend and no accounts. Every tool (JSON formatter, Base64
          encoder, JWT decoder, hash generator, and the rest) runs entirely in your
          browser using standard JavaScript and Web APIs. Whatever you type or paste
          into a tool is processed locally on your device and is never transmitted to
          or stored on any server.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
        <h2 style="margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-size:1.1rem;">Analytics</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin:0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">
          Bracketly uses Cloudflare Web Analytics to understand overall site traffic
          (which pages are visited, roughly how many people visit). It's cookieless
          and doesn't build a profile of individual visitors — Cloudflare's own
          documentation covers exactly what it collects.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
        <h2 style="margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-size:1.1rem;">Advertising</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin:0 0 0.9rem;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">
          Bracketly shows ads served by Google AdSense to help cover hosting costs.
          Google and its advertising partners may use cookies or similar
          technologies to serve ads, including ads based on your prior visits to
          this or other websites. Bracketly itself does not access or store any
          data these cookies collect.
        </p>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin:0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">
          You can see and adjust what Google knows for ad personalization at{" "}
          <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">adssettings.google.com</a>,
          and read Google's own policy at{" "}
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/technologies/ads</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <h2 style="margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-size:1.1rem;">Questions</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin:0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">
          Bracketly is open-source. If you have a question about this policy or want
          to check exactly what a page loads, the full source is on{" "}
          <a href="https://github.com/GRimkiller360/bracketly" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
